<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Wentzel, Willard Ferdinand. A Continuation of the Journal of the Forks Mackenzie's River for Summer 1807-1808. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0022</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p></p>
<p class="head">June 1808</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Gave the Capot Rouge a Chiefs Coat a Shirt &amp; a Brayet in consideration of his good behaviour in seconding me so effectually in getting so many Indians above &#8211; for I must please him as he is the principal head &amp; at the same time the only one who Knows that Country thoroughly &#8211; besides an interested Indian, a good Hunter, and I dare say if displeased would be an <span style="text-decoration:underline;">illustrous</span> <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Coquin</span><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>gain if he should be sent away any ways dissati<span class="AddHand-author">s</span>fied, a word only would be sufficient to dest<span class="AddHand-author">r</span>oy all our hopes of making a good number of Packs next year<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Particularly as the Indians are but just departed from the Fond Lakes to which they often cast a languishing look to return<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I gave the Levrier who is also a would be Chief &#8211; one of my Eq<sup>t</sup> Handkerchief<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Gave Gratis in Trade &amp;<sup>c</sup> &amp;<sup>c</sup> altogether Chiefs included &#8211; 17 meas Am<sup>n</sup> 1 fm Tob<sup>o</sup> &amp; 14 flints 2 Awls &amp; 4 needles &#8211; 1 Skeen thread<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  My Slave Hunter brought 2 Swans 14 Ducks 4 Cranes 1 bustard &amp; 4 Loons<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The men pressed the remainder of the Packs that were ready for the Press<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Weighed 4 more to day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tues<sup>y</sup> 1<sup>st</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Gave Six more Packs made &amp; Pressed &#8211; the whole am<sup>t</sup> now in Store consists of 33 Packs &amp; a remainder<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednes<sup>y</sup> 2<sup>nd</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent all the young men with Beaulieux to Hunt<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[G]</span>ave them 8 meas: Am<sup>n</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afternoon Bessemoi who had his nose wrung in the month of Dec<sup>r</sup> &#8211; brought &amp; Traded 15 Pichoux &amp; 1 B<sup>r</sup> Capot value 11 Skins<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent him off again<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Fine weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thurs<sup>y</sup> 3<sup>rd</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Arrived two young men from Grand Chefres band, they left the old Gentleman after the visit had been returned to the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Embayodinnais</span>, Since them they have not been with him<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hey could not by this give me any news about Jollibois, concerning whom I begin to be a little uneasy<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>hese Indians gave 17½ Skins of debts in furrs &amp; Traded 23 Skins in furrs more<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent them off again &amp; desired that they should</p>

